text: Oooh, on my reading list. Had an interesting conversation the other day about whether or not to personify bots. Siri seems like a snob while "Ok Google" has no persona but is very friendly

Biggest takeaway quote for me: "But it would be naïve to ignore the motives of the companies building these products. Amazon wants to sell you things (after all, its design guidelines identify Alexa owners not as “users” but “customers”), and a more emotive assistant could be leveraged to that end."
